msgid "Publication patterns"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"lead\">The following section sets out a number of publication "
"patterns that will increase the usability of data for users.</span>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:0
msgid "Basic"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:0
msgid "Licensing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:11
msgid ""
"Publishing data under an open licenses is an important part of open "
"contracting. Without this, restrictions on re-use may prevent many of the "
"important use cases for open contracting information being realised."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:13
msgid ""
"A license statement sets out the permission that users have to access, use "
"and re-use the data. This can take the form of a Public Domain Dedication or"
" Certification which transfers a dataset into the public domain, or re-"
"asserts that there are no existing copyrights or database rights inherent in"
" the dataset (which is the case for government datasets in some "
"jurisdictions), or the application of a license which sets out the terms "
"under which a dataset may be re-used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:15
msgid ""
"We recommend the use of either a public domain dedication/certification, or "
"an attribution only license."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:20
msgid ""
"When using custom licenses, publishers are encouraged to check that they are"
" compliant with the Open Definition."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:22
msgid ""
"In structured data file you can embed a link to the license in the license "
"field of the release or record package. In individual CSV files or other "
"models of publishing, it may not be possible to embed the license "
"information. In these cases (and in the structured data case also) "
"publishers should ensure that a clear statement is provided alongside files "
"where they are provided for download linking to, and explaining, the license"
" terms they are under. Particular attention should be paid to ensuring "
"license information on any data catalogues where open contracting data is "
"listed are accurate."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:0
msgid "Publication policy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:26
msgid ""
"Publishing Open Contracting data involves making a number of choices about "
"what data and documents to include and how to classify and categorise "
"different items. To allow users to understand the choices that a publisher "
"has made, a publisher should provide a public web page or document that "
"details the decisions they have made concerning the issues listed below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:28
msgid ""
"This document should also contain information about future plans for changes"
" to the data and who to contact with enquiries about the data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:30
msgid "Publication policy pages should include information about:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:38
msgid ""
"Publishers may also wish to apply for, and include the results of, an Open "
"Data Certificate, on their publication policy pages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:0
msgid "Flat CSV file options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:42
msgid ""
"The serialization section provides information on publishing data as flat "
"CSV files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:0
msgid "Intermediate"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:0
msgid "Release and record URIs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:50
msgid ""
"To achieve 3 and 4 ☆ ODCS publication, publishers should provide data in "
"files following the full OCDS schema, and either with releases and records "
"provided in bulk (3 ☆), or with each release at it's own unique URI (4 ☆)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:0
msgid "Provide full records"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:56
msgid ""
"A basic OCDS record can list the releases related to a given contracting "
"process. However, a full record will provide a compiled release, showing the"
" current state of the contracting process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:0
msgid "User-friendly publication"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:60
msgid ""
"The release and record data package containers (in JSON and CSV) offer a way"
" to provide bulk access to a collection of contracting process release and "
"records. However, very large files can be difficult for users to download "
"and process. The following section provides suggested good practices which "
"will assist users in accessing data. These are not requirements of the "
"standard, but are based on experiences of maximising the number of users "
"able to work with datasets with their existing hardware and software."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:0
msgid "File size limits"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:64
msgid ""
"When generating data packages for bulk download, apply the following limits:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:70
msgid ""
"When a file is likely to exceed one of these limits, release or records "
"should be split across multiple files. Dynamically generated bulk downloads "
"do not have to apply these limits, though publishers should consider ways to"
" advise users when a query is likely to generate a very large file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:0
msgid "Segmenting files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:74
msgid ""
"When the suggested limits require publication of multiple files, publishers "
"should consider ways to split data across available files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:76
msgid "For releases, publishers may choose to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:81
msgid ""
"For records, publishers should segment either based on the first releaseDate"
" associated with a contracting process, or by contracting process "
"identifier."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:83
msgid ""
"Following these approaches will avoid release and records moving between "
"files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:0
msgid "Compression"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:87
msgid ""
"OCDS data packages may be compressed in order to save on diskspace and "
"bandwidth."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:89
msgid ""
"If compressing data packages, publishers should use the zip file format."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:0
msgid "Serving files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:93
msgid ""
"Publishers should ensure that the web server providing access to bulk files "
"correctly reports the HTTP Last-Modified header so that consuming "
"applications only need to download updated files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:0
msgid "Advanced"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:0
msgid "Supporting discovery"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:100
msgid ""
"There are many thousands of organisations who should be able to publish Open"
" Contracting data. As a result, maintaining a central registry of all "
"published data is impractical. Instead, OCDS proposes a common pattern for "
"the discovery of Open Contracting data releases and records."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:102
msgid ""
"For the discovery of bulk datasets, and the location of any data feeds, we "
"propose use of a data.json file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:104
msgid ""
"For the discovery of individual releases and records, we propose use atom "
"feeds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:0
msgid "Dataset and feed discovery"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:108
msgid ""
"Publishers should provide a data.json document describing the location of "
"all of the bulk OCDS files available for download."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:110
msgid ""
"This should follow the structure proposed by the US Project Open Data with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:116
msgid ""
"In addition, the data.json document may contain one or more records with the"
" keyword 'open-contracting-feed' and either 'open-contracting-release' or "
"'open-contracting-record' and pointing via an accessURL in their "
"distribution block to an atom feed document."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:0
msgid "Feeds"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:120
msgid ""
"Publishers exposing individual records and releases, of regularly updated "
"data packages in small sets, should provide one or more atom feeds that "
"index these, and provide an easy mechanism for users to discover recently "
"published or updated release and records."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:122
msgid ""
"The link to the release or record should be provided via a <link> tag, and "
"the updated date of the entry should reflect the updated date of that "
"release or record. The <id> should reflect the release id for release, or "
"the ocid for records."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:124
msgid ""
"The release.tag should be contained within a <category> element of the feed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:126
msgid ""
"Feeds requiring pagination should follow the approach set out in RFC 5005."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:0
msgid "Well Known"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:130
msgid ""
"Future implementations of OCDS will explore use of the <a "
"href=\"http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5785\">/.well-known/</a> protocol to "
"declare a location for storing a data.json file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:132
msgid ""
"At present, such files can be hosted anywhere, and consuming applications "
"pointed towards them manually."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:134
msgid ""
"The data.json structure has been chosen to allow organisations following "
"this approach to include tagged 'open-contracting-data' within their "
"existing data discovery mechanisms, and given the availability of a plugin "
"for the widely used CKAN which will also support exposure of data.json "
"files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:0
msgid "Linking data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/implementation/publication_patterns.md:138
msgid ""
"For 5 ☆ publication of OCDS data, publishers should seek to use URIs in "
"their datasets, linking to other machine-readable data sources at an entity-"
"by-entity level."
msgstr ""
